Summary: My FinalWriter Macros didn't work until now.
Keywords: AREXX FinalWriter Word Processing
X-Newsreader: TIN [version 1.1 PL8]

None of my AREXX Scripts nor the supplied FinalWriter AREXX
macros functioned. Calls to SoftWood and help from netters
yielded no solution to this 'mysterious' bug. 

I found the answer just a couple of hours ago: The pathname
of the directory in which I placed FinalWriter was too long!
I had put it in with my other word processing files in...

Programs:Applications/Word_Processing/FinalWriter

Now, this doesn't look too long to me, but everything rexx-wise
became fully funtional when I moved the whole FinalWriter
directory to the root directory. Before that REXX did absolutely
nothing...not even error messages.

